Now here is how to add it to your server, this model is fully animated and by following the exact steps in the following tutorial, we are going to create a special attack for this model and bonuses.

[b]Step 1:[/b]

Download this file: http://uppit.com/v/pq5t7npi and extract it. You will see 4 files, 2 that end with .gz and 2 that end with .mqo. The .mqo's are the wear and drop/inventory models for the ones who want to recolour the model and the .dat's are the wear and drop/inventory models for in-game. Open up you client's folder and copy both of the [b].GZ[/b] models in there.

[b]Step 2:[/b]

Open up Class8.java in your client's folder and scroll down until you see something like this:

	[code]if(i == 13634) {
	class8.aStringArray189 = new String[5];
	class8.aStringArray189[1] = "Wear";
	class8.anInt174 = 14041; //Inv & Ground
	class8.anInt181 = 2000; //Zoom
	class8.anInt190 = 572;
	class8.anInt198 = 1200;
	class8.anInt204 = 0;
	class8.anInt169 = 16;
	class8.anInt194 = 1;
	class8.anInt165 = 14042; //Male
	class8.anInt200 = 14042; //Female
	class8.anInt175 = -1;
	class8.anInt197 = -1;
	class8.anInt199 = -1;//noteable
	class8.aString170 = "Bandos Shield";
	class8.aByteArray178 = "A Defence tool used by ancient bandos".getBytes();
	}[/code]

And right under that add this:

[code]if (i == 8006) // Your desired item id (the one you use after pickup ##### #)
{
        class8.aStringArray189 = new String[5];
        class8.aStringArray189[1] = "wield"; //
        class8.anInt174 = 8007; //DropInv Model
        class8.anInt165 = 8006; //Male Wield Model
        class8.anInt200 = 8006; //Female Wield
        class8.anInt188 = -1; //Male armssleeves (Leave as -1 if not used)
        class8.anInt164 = -1; //Female armssleeves (Leave as -1 if not used)
        class8.anInt181 = 800; //Zoom - Increase to make inv model smaller
        class8.anInt190 = 720; //Rotate updown - Increase to rotate upwards
        class8.anInt198 = 504; //Rotate rightleft - Increase to rotate right
        class8.anInt169 = -1; //Position in inv, increase to move right
        class8.anInt194 = -1; //Position in inv, increase to move up
        class8.aString170 = "The Scythe of Eleanor"; //Item Name
        class8.aByteArray178 = "A legendary scythe made by Vreg/MistaBigBoss.".getBytes(); //Item Examine
}[/code]

After you've done that save and compile, we're done for the client part.

[b]Step 3:[/b]

Open up item.cfg and scroll down untill you see the last item and right below that add this, this is for the bonuses:

[code]item = 8006	The Scythe of Eleanor	A legendary scythe made by Vreg/MistaBigBoss.	5000000	5000000	5000000	115	135	129	-4	-1	0	4	5	0	0	110	0[/code]

After you've done that save and close item.cfg.

[b]Step 4:[/b]

Open client.java in your server's folder and search for:

[code]SpecDamg(30);[/code]

And you will see something like this:

[code]public void hally()
   {
       if(IsAttackingNPC && playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 3204)
       {
           setAnimation(440);
           actionTimer = 4;
           SpecDamgNPC(30);
    DDS2Damg = true;
    DDStimer = 1;
    resetAnimation();
           teleportToX = absX;
           teleportToY = absY;
           SpecDamgNPC(30);
    SpecialDelay -= 1;
       } else
       if(IsAttacking && playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 3204)
       {
           int j = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].absX;
           int k = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].absY;
           int l = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].playerLevel[playerHitpoints];
           SpecDamg(30);
    DDS2Damg = true;
    DDStimer = 1;
           startAnimation(440);
           actionTimer = 4;
           teleportToX = absX;
           teleportToY = absY;
           SpecialDelay -= 1;
       }
}[/code]

Right below that add this, this is for the special attack:

[code]public void scytheofeleanor()
   {
       if(IsAttackingNPC && playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 8006)
